# ESP32 Smart Kallax

This ESP32 platformIO project is meant to manage the mm Wave sensor LD2411s and a PWM 12V output in order to light a wardrobe when presence is detected, with integration to Home Assistant

## Features

- MQTT client support
- Motion detection
- soft turn on and turn off the led strip
- integration with Home Assistant

## Usage

This project needs the complementary libraries that can be found [here](https://github.com/eeyteo/ESP32_custom_libs).
Add the needed reference in platformio.ini
```xml
lib_extra_dirs = ..\PlatformIO\Libs
```
You can find more detailed information (and the fabricazion files) on my [website](https://cortimatteo.it) and a step by step guide on the [video tutorial]().

You'll need to add config.h file with the defines

```xml
#pragma once
#define SSID "your ssid"
#define PASSWORD "your passwprd"
```

## Hardware
1. ESP32 development board is needed.
2. LM25T5-5 for generating 5v
3. IRLZ44N forr driving the logic level mosfet
4. LD2411s for detecting.
5. custom PCB

